[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":222},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F":198,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F":207},"\u002FSCSS\u002F20190421\u002F968240674\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":8,"body":9,"category":181,"date":182,"description":183,"extension":184,"lang":185,"meta":186,"navigation":187,"path":188,"readingMinutes":189,"seo":190,"standalone":191,"stem":192,"tags":193,"tldr":195,"updated":195,"url":196,"__hash__":197},"content\u002Fen\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin.md","SCSS Handbook (5) — mixin","9682406740","\u002Fscss\u002F20190421\u002F968240674\u002F",{"type":10,"value":11,"toc":175},"minimark",[12,17,30,33,36,43,49,58,65,70,76,81,84,89,92,104,109,125,130,136,141,148,153,156,161,164,170],[13,14,16],"h2",{"id":15},"intro","Intro",[18,19,20,21,25,26,29],"p",{},"The previous post covered ",[22,23,24],"code",{},"@import",". This one combines what we've learned so far and introduces ",[22,27,28],{},"mixin",". What's a mixin?\nI think of it as an SCSS library — a place to store SCSS snippets I use often.",[13,31,32],{"id":28},"Mixin",[18,34,35],{},"Why \"frequently used SCSS\"? If you had to write CSS to hide text right now off the top of your head, could you remember the exact code?",[18,37,38],{},[39,40],"img",{"alt":41,"src":42},"image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FnbCv2i5.png",[18,44,45,46,48],{},"Maybe — but your brain has limited memory, especially for things you don't use that often. Having to remember stuff like this every time is inefficient. That's where ",[22,47,28],{}," shines — it lets you package CSS.",[18,50,51,52,54,55,57],{},"Think of a ",[22,53,28],{}," as a way to wrap up frequently used CSS into a class — just like writing CSS classes. So let's write a ",[22,56,28],{}," for hiding text.",[18,59,60,61,64],{},"First create a new file ",[22,62,63],{},"_mixin.scss",":",[18,66,67],{},[39,68],{"alt":41,"src":69},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F9425213.png",[18,71,72,73,75],{},"The syntax for ",[22,74,28],{}," is super simple:",[18,77,78],{},[39,79],{"alt":41,"src":80},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPaKZUr5.png",[18,82,83],{},"Drop the text-hide CSS inside:",[18,85,86],{},[39,87],{"alt":41,"src":88},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FcJD4U7f.png",[18,90,91],{},"Name it semantically — don't pick weird names you can't remember, that defeats the point.",[18,93,94,95,97,98,100,101,64],{},"How do you import your ",[22,96,28],{}," into your other SCSS? That's where ",[22,99,24],{}," from the previous post comes in. Import in ",[22,102,103],{},"_layout.scss",[18,105,106],{},[39,107],{"alt":41,"src":108},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F8gTpXnk.png",[18,110,111,112,116,117,120,121,124],{},"One detail — to ",[113,114,115],"em",{},"use"," a mixin, write ",[22,118,119],{},"@include + name",". So to use the ",[22,122,123],{},"text-hide"," mixin we just wrote:",[18,126,127],{},[39,128],{"alt":41,"src":129},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FGG8aD2H.png",[18,131,132,133,64],{},"After compiling, you'll see the hide-text CSS from the mixin compiled into ",[22,134,135],{},".logo",[18,137,138],{},[39,139],{"alt":41,"src":140},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXv0yJk6.png",[18,142,143,144,147],{},"You can also write shorter mixins for quick everyday styling. Like — we use ",[22,145,146],{},"background-size: cover;"," a lot, so we can wrap it in a mixin:",[18,149,150],{},[39,151],{"alt":41,"src":152},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FmmA1lMP.png",[18,154,155],{},"Or responsive image CSS:",[18,157,158],{},[39,159],{"alt":41,"src":160},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FxccFKIM.png",[18,162,163],{},"These all reduce the amount you need to memorize and speed up development.",[18,165,166,169],{},[22,167,168],{},"@mixin"," also supports parameters:",[18,171,172],{},[39,173],{"alt":41,"src":174},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FrUwC2sY.png",{"title":176,"searchDepth":177,"depth":177,"links":178},"",2,[179,180],{"id":15,"depth":177,"text":16},{"id":28,"depth":177,"text":32},"SCSS","2019-04-21 07:24:30","The previous post covered `@import`. This one starts pulling in earlier topics, building up to `mixin`. What's a mixin? I think of it as an SCSS library — a place to store frequently used SCSS snippets.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin","2",{"title":6,"description":183},false,"en\u002FSCSS\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin",[181,194],"SCSS Handbook",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fscss-handbook-5-mixin\u002F","Wq3csOaV4HcTqimPG7PieoWPyV41PDS3w5w1Q78sVcY",{"newer":199,"older":203},{"url":200,"title":201,"date":202},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F21\u002Fjavascript-array-20-methods\u002F","20 Ways to Work With JavaScript Arrays (And Which Ones Mutate the Original)","2019-04-21 11:56:53",{"url":204,"title":205,"date":206},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fjavascript-hoisting-01-explained\u002F","JavaScript Hoisting: Why Does That Variable Say undefined?","2019-04-19 20:33:08",[208,213,217],{"url":209,"title":210,"date":211,"readingMinutes":212},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2025\u002F11\u002F23\u002Fsass-deprecated-import-use-forward-migration\u002F","SCSS Is Deprecating @import?!","2025-11-23 15:32:01","4",{"url":214,"title":215,"date":216,"readingMinutes":189},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F19\u002Fscss-handbook-4-import\u002F","SCSS Handbook (4) — @import","2019-04-19 17:24:30",{"url":218,"title":219,"date":220,"readingMinutes":221},"\u002Fen\u002Fscss\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F18\u002Fscss-handbook-3-operators\u002F","SCSS Handbook (3) — Operators","2019-04-18 17:24:30","1",1784010287581]